import React, { Component } from 'react' // import '../CSS/EmployeeDetails.css'; import '../components/styles/EmployeeDetails.css'; import config from '../config' export default class EmployeeDetails extends Component { constructor(props){ super(props); this.state = { id : this.props.match.params.Emp_id, Employee: [] } } componentDidMount() { fetch(config.drupal_url+'/lister/Employees/'+this.state.id) .then(x => x.json()) .then(x => this.setState({ Employee: x })); } render() { let Employees = this.state.Employee; return (
{ Employees.map(x => (

Employee Details

Name: { x.name }
Emp Id: { x.Emp_id }
Designation: { x.role }
Experience: { x.Experience } years
Manager: { x.Manager }
Current project: { x.Project }
Current working project: { x.field_current_working_project }
Project History: { x.Project_history }
Previous company: { x.Previous_company }
certifications: { x.certifications }
Accomplishments: {x.accomplishments.map(y => ( y +'. ' ))}
Primary skills: { x.Primary_skills } {x.Primary_skills_rating}
Secondary skills: { x.Secondary_skills }
Primary skills2: { JSON.stringify(x.field_primary_skills) } { x.field_primary_skills }
Tools familiar: { x.field_tools_familiar }
)) }
); } }
